From George Ferguson Subject Xarchie available on export Please accept the following announcement for gf A completely revamped version of the browser interface to Archie Xarchie is now available as contrib xarchie For those not familar with Archie or Xarchie I include part of the manpage intro Xarchie is an browser interface to the Archie Internet information system using the Prospero virtual filesystem Archie provides information about files available for ftp anywhere on the Internet Xarchie displays this information using an easy to use point and click Xarchie allows you to further explore ftp sites by examining directories returned as query matches and allows you to retrieve files located this Xarchie has been extensively tested on and a variety of other flavors of X and on a wide range of A summary of the new features from the README follows Major improvements include Multiple selections allowed in browser for use with other new features FWF MultiList widget Ability to expand directories in Real fully integrated ftp Ability to save and reload query results as well as print Ability to resort results and sort results by user definable pseudo Online help Color resources done so that they don't break mono FWF FileSelector widget for local file 's supplied for the imake George George Ferguson ARPA of Computer Science UUCP rutgers rochester ferguson University of Rochester VOX Rochester NY FAX